%h1.title Sign your certificate
.content
  %ol
    %li
      Download
      %strong Root Certificate
    %li
      Create
      %strong Certificate Signing Request
      %blockquote openssl req -new -newkey rsa:2048 -subj "/C=UA/O=My Org/CN=My name" -keyout myprivate.key -out mysigningrequest.csr
    %li
      Upload
      %strong Certificate Signing Request
      and get chain of certificates
      %blockquote wget --header="Content-Type: text/plain" --post-file mysigningrequest.csr #{api_v1_certificates_url(format: :text)}
      First certificate is your new certificate, second - intermitiate CA that had issued certificates. extract content in favorite text editor
    %li You can verificate you
    %blockquote openssl verify -CApath mycert.crt subca.crt ./projects/certificate_authority/public/root.crt

%h1.title Listing certificates

%table.table.is-striped
  %thead
    %tr
      %th Serial
      %th Applicant
      %th Issuance date
      %th

  %tbody
    - presenter.certificates.each do |certificate|
      %tr
        %td= certificate.serial
        %td= certificate.name
        %td= certificate.date
        %td= certificate.revoke_button

%br
